# Walkthrough — Sentiment Liquidity Engine

## Phase 1: Core Infrastructure ✅
Built foundational layers: type definitions, `puter.kv` TTL wrapper, exponential backoff, per-source circuit breakers, atomic distributed locking via `puter.kv.incr()`, `puter.ai` model wrapper (zero developer API keys), and ticker validation.

## Phase 2: Feed Ingestion & Pipeline ✅

### Feed Layer
- **RSS Parser** — Browser-native `DOMParser` for RSS 2.0 / Atom XML
- **JSON Parser** — Supports JSON Feed 1.1 and common API shapes
- **18 Curated Sources** — Tier 1 (Reuters, CNBC, WSJ), Tier 2 (Yahoo, CoinDesk), Tier 3 (Fed Reserve, IMF)
- **Feed Index** — Coordinator with circuit-breaker and backoff integration

### 6-Stage AI Pipeline
| Stage | File | Purpose |
|-------|------|---------|
| 0 | [stage0-dedup.ts](file:///c:/Users/hardi/Documents/Resume/RTF/lib/pipeline/stage0-dedup.ts) | SHA256 exact + semantic embedding dedup (decreasing timestamp keys) |
| 1 | [stage1-prefilter.ts](file:///c:/Users/hardi/Documents/Resume/RTF/lib/pipeline/stage1-prefilter.ts) | Batched relevance filter (Gemini Flash, 16/call) |
| 2a | [stage2a-ner.ts](file:///c:/Users/hardi/Documents/Resume/RTF/lib/pipeline/stage2a-ner.ts) | NER + ticker extraction (Gemini Pro → GPT-4o-mini fallback) |
| 2b | [stage2b-disambiguate.ts](file:///c:/Users/hardi/Documents/Resume/RTF/lib/pipeline/stage2b-disambiguate.ts) | Keyword co-occurrence disambiguation |
| 3 | [stage3-sentiment.ts](file:///c:/Users/hardi/Documents/Resume/RTF/lib/pipeline/stage3-sentiment.ts) | Per-ticker scoring (Claude Sonnet → DeepSeek fallback) |
| 4 | [stage4-aggregation.ts](file:///c:/Users/hardi/Documents/Resume/RTF/lib/pipeline/stage4-aggregation.ts) | EWMA aggregation with atomic locking |
| 5 | [stage5-snapshot.ts](file:///c:/Users/hardi/Documents/Resume/RTF/lib/pipeline/stage5-snapshot.ts) | Hourly KV snapshots + pipeline stats |

### Pipeline Orchestrator
- Concurrency-limited processing (10 parallel articles)
- Dead Letter Queue for failed articles
- Global watchlist maintenance

### Puter Workers (self-contained JS)
- [manager.js](file:///c:/Users/hardi/Documents/Resume/RTF/puter-worker/manager.js) — Fan-out coordinator with anti-spam guard
- [fetcher.js](file:///c:/Users/hardi/Documents/Resume/RTF/puter-worker/fetcher.js) — Feed group fetcher with inline circuit breakers
- [pipeline.js](file:///c:/Users/hardi/Documents/Resume/RTF/puter-worker/pipeline.js) — Full Stage 0→5 pipeline with inline AI helpers

### Key Constraints Enforced
- ✅ `puter.workers.execute()` (not `.run()`)
- ✅ `puter.kv.incr()` atomic locks (not get→set)
- ✅ Decreasing timestamp prefix for semantic cache ordering
- ✅ Zero developer API keys — all inference via `puter.ai`
